-- U.S. Stocks Gain, Treasuries Drop as Fed’s Bernanke Sees Economic Growth
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2012-02-02T15:06:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/u-s-stocks-gain-treasuries-drop-as-fed-s-bernanke-sees-economic-growth.html
U.S. stocks gained and Treasuries
retreated after Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  said he
sees signs the economy is improving.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index rose 0.2 percent to
1,326.17 at 10:05 a.m. in  New York . The yield on the 10-year
U.S. Treasury note climbed two basis points to 1.84 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael P. Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  